The earthquake which hit northern Chiletoday, registering 7.0 on the open-ended Richter scale, causedno damage to the copper mine at Chuquicamata, a mine spokesmansaid.    Chuquicamata public relations director Guillermo Barcelotold Reuters by telephone from the mine that the quake hadcaused no problems and operations continued as usual.    A spokesman for the state Chilean Copper Commission inSantiago confirmed there had been no damage at Chuquicamata. Reuter&#3;